I can’t scaffold or edit the project while **Ask mode** is on — only explain and give you a blueprint. Switch to **Agent mode** if you want this built in your workspace automatically.

Below is a concrete plan for a **dynamic, modern Next.js stock dashboard** with portfolio tracking and charts.

---

## Recommended stack

| Layer | Choice |
|--------|--------|
| Framework | **Next.js 15** (App Router) |
| UI | **Tailwind CSS** + **shadcn/ui** |
| Charts | **Recharts** or **Lightweight Charts** (TradingView-style) |
| Data | **Alpha Vantage** / **Finnhub** / **Polygon** (free tiers) or mock data for dev |
| State | **Zustand** or React Context for portfolio |
| Animations | **Framer Motion** |

---

## Features to build

1. **Dashboard home** — market summary, watchlist tickers, portfolio value card with % change
2. **Portfolio** — holdings (symbol, shares, avg cost, current price, P&amp;L)
3. **Charts** — line/candlestick per symbol, timeframe selector (1D / 1W / 1M / 1Y)
4. **Add/remove positions** — form or modal
5. **Dark theme** — glassmorphism cards, subtle gradients, live number animations

---

## Project structure

```text
app/
  layout.tsx          # dark theme, fonts (Geist/Inter)
  page.tsx            # dashboard
  portfolio/page.tsx
  api/quotes/route.ts # proxy to avoid exposing API keys
components/
  DashboardHeader.tsx
  PortfolioSummary.tsx
  HoldingsTable.tsx
  StockChart.tsx
  Watchlist.tsx
  AddPositionDialog.tsx
lib/
  portfolio-store.ts
  mock-data.ts
  types.ts
```

---

## Core types

```typescript
// lib/types.ts
export type Holding = {
  symbol: string;
  shares: number;
  avgCost: number;
};

export type Quote = {
  symbol: string;
  price: number;
  change: number;
  changePercent: number;
};

export type PortfolioSnapshot = {
  totalValue: number;
  totalCost: number;
  dayChange: number;
  dayChangePercent: number;
  holdings: (Holding & { quote: Quote; marketValue: number; pl: number; plPercent: number })[];
};
```

---

## Portfolio logic (example)

```typescript
// lib/portfolio.ts
import type { Holding, Quote } from "./types";

export function computePortfolio(holdings: Holding[], quotes: Record<string, Quote>) {
  let totalValue = 0;
  let totalCost = 0;

  const enriched = holdings.map((h) => {
    const q = quotes[h.symbol];
    const price = q?.price ?? 0;
    const marketValue = price * h.shares;
    const cost = h.avgCost * h.shares;
    const pl = marketValue - cost;
    totalValue += marketValue;
    totalCost += cost;
    return {
      ...h,
      quote: q,
      marketValue,
      pl,
      plPercent: cost ? (pl / cost) * 100 : 0,
    };
  });

  const totalPl = totalValue - totalCost;
  const dayChange = enriched.reduce(
    (sum, h) => sum + (h.quote?.change ?? 0) * h.shares,
    0
  );

  return {
    totalValue,
    totalCost,
    totalPl,
    totalPlPercent: totalCost ? (totalPl / totalCost) * 100 : 0,
    dayChange,
    dayChangePercent: totalValue ? (dayChange / totalValue) * 100 : 0,
    holdings: enriched,
  };
}
```

---

## Modern UI direction

- **Background:** `bg-zinc-950` with radial gradients (`from-emerald-500/10 via-transparent`)
- **Cards:** `backdrop-blur`, `border border-white/10`, hover glow on watchlist rows
- **Numbers:** animate with Framer Motion when quotes refresh
- **Chart:** gradient area fill under line; green/red by trend
- **Typography:** large tabular nums for prices (`font-mono tabular-nums`)

Example summary card layout:

```tsx
// components/PortfolioSummary.tsx (conceptual)
<div className="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6 backdrop-blur-xl">
  <p className="text-sm text-zinc-400">Portfolio value</p>
  <p className="text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight">${totalValue.toLocaleString()}</p>
  <p className={dayChange >= 0 ? "text-emerald-400" : "text-rose-400"}>
    {dayChange >= 0 ? "+" : ""}{dayChange.toFixed(2)} ({dayChangePercent.toFixed(2)}%) today
  </p>
</div>
```

---

## Chart component (Recharts)

```tsx
// components/StockChart.tsx — simplified
"use client";
import { AreaChart, Area, XAxis, YAxis, Tooltip, ResponsiveContainer } from "recharts";

export function StockChart({ data }: { data: { date: string; close: number }[] }) {
  const up = data.length > 1 && data.at(-1)!.close >= data[0]!.close;
  const color = up ? "#34d399" : "#fb7185";

  return (
    <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={320}>
      <AreaChart data={data}>
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="fill" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
            <stop offset="0%" stopColor={color} stopOpacity={0.4} />
            <stop offset="100%" stopColor={color} stopOpacity={0} />
          </linearGradient>
        </defs>
        <XAxis dataKey="date" hide />
        <YAxis domain={["auto", "auto"]} hide />
        <Tooltip contentStyle={{ background: "#18181b", border: "1px solid #3f3f46" }} />
        <Area type="monotone" dataKey="close" stroke={color} fill="url(#fill)" strokeWidth={2} />
      </AreaChart>
    </ResponsiveContainer>
  );
}
```

---

## API route (keep keys server-side)

```typescript
// app/api/quotes/route.ts
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";

export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const { searchParams } = new URL(request.url);
  const symbols = searchParams.get("symbols")?.split(",") ?? [];
  // Fetch from Finnhub/Alpha Vantage, or return mock in dev
  const quotes = Object.fromEntries(
    symbols.map((s) => [s, { symbol: s, price: 100 + Math.random() * 50, change: 1.2, changePercent: 0.5 }])
  );
  return NextResponse.json(quotes);
}
```

---

## Quick start commands (when you build it)

```bash
npx create-next-app@latest stock-dashboard --typescript --tailwind --eslint --app
cd stock-dashboard
npx shadcn@latest init
npm install recharts framer-motion zustand
```

Persist portfolio in `localStorage` via Zustand `persist` middleware for a demo without a database.

---

## What I’d implement in Agent mode

1. Bootstrap Next.js + Tailwind + shadcn  
2. Dark dashboard layout with sidebar (Dashboard / Portfolio)  
3. Zustand portfolio store + add-position dialog  
4. Mock quotes API + optional real API env vars  
5. Recharts on dashboard + per-symbol detail  
6. Framer Motion on stat cards and table rows  

**Switch to Agent mode** and say where to create the project (e.g. `C:\Users\sante\projects\stock-dashboard`) and whether you want **mock data only** or a specific API key — I can then generate the full app for you.

